<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
Berlese described 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hermanniidae" genus="Hermannia" genus.bestMatchDistance="26" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">H. grandis</taxonomicName>
after a nymph from Filettino (near Rome). According to the diagnosis the length of the specimen is 1.000 mm and the breadth 0.640. The type-slide (no. 103/13) is still present in the Collection, but it is in a bad condition and completely dark.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
